## Link Validation Checklist
Before committing changes:

### Check Main README Links
- [ ] All table of contents links work correctly
- [ ] Section descriptions match actual page content
- [ ] No broken internal references

### Check Cross-References
- [ ] Security standard references are current
- [ ] API documentation links are valid
- [ ] Tool references point to correct pages
- [ ] Operation guide links work

### Check Navigation
- [ ] All pages have proper navigation footers
- [ ] Previous/Next relationships form valid chains
- [ ] No orphaned pages without navigation

### Check Asset References
- [ ] Image references use correct paths
- [ ] CSS imports are valid
- [ ] No broken asset links

## Automated Link Checking
Use these patterns to find potential issues:

### Find Markdown Links
```bash
# Find all markdown links
grep -r "\[.*\](.*\.md)" pages/
```

### Find Relative Path Issues
```bash
# Find potential path issues
grep -r "\.\./\.\." pages/
```

### Find Hardcoded References
```bash
# Find absolute URLs that should be relative
grep -r "https://github.com/MYOB-Technology/MYOB-AI-Codex" pages/
```

## Common Link Update Scenarios

### When Adding New Page
1. Add to appropriate README section navigation chain
2. Update previous page's "Next" link to new page
3. Update new page's "Previous" link to previous page
4. Update next page's "Previous" link to new page
5. Add cross-references from related pages
6. Update main [README.md](mdc:README.md) table of contents

### When Renaming/Moving Page
1. Search and replace ALL references to old filename
2. Update navigation chains
3. Update main [README.md](mdc:README.md) table of contents
4. Check for references in assets or configuration files

### When Removing Page
1. Remove from navigation chain
2. Update previous page's "Next" link to skip removed page
3. Update next page's "Previous" link to skip removed page  
4. Remove cross-references from other pages
5. Update main [README.md](mdc:README.md) table of contents